// Exercise 1: Calculate the Sum of Two Numbers

 Start
 Enter num1, num2.
 Read values of num1 and num2.
 Add num1 and num 2. 
      num1+num2=sum
 Display sum.
 End


// Exercise 2: Check if a Number is Even or Odd

 Start
 Enter num.
 Read value of num.
 Divide num by 2.
IF remainder is 0, display "Even number".
ELSE display "Odd number".
 End


// Exercise 3: 
Write pseudo code that will perform the following.    

a) Read in 5 separate numbers. 
b) Calculate the average of the five numbers.
c) Find the smallest (minimum) and largest (maximum) of the five entered numbers.
d) Write out the results found from steps b and c with a message describing what they are

a)Enter num1, num2, num3, num4, num5
  Read num1, num2, num3, num4, num5

b)Add num1+num2+num3+num4+num5=sum
  Divide the sum by 5
       sum/5=avg
  Display avg

c)Small=n1  
  Large=n1
  for i=2 to 5:
    IF n1>ni then:
      small=ni
    IF n1<ni then:
      large=ni

d)Display ("Average:",avg)
  Display ("Smallest:",min)
  Display ("Largest:",max)

-- END --
